article.headline: Dartmouth 55, Army 42
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Mike Lang scored 17 points and Leon Pattman added 12 points off the bench as Dartmouth beat Army 55-42 on Wednesday night. Down 20-19 at halftime, Dartmouth (2-9) used a 17-9 run in the first 7 minutes of the second half to take a 36-26 lead. Lang made three 3-pointers during the spurt for the Big Green, who snapped an eight-game losing streak. Pattman didn't play in the first half because of an injury. Army (4-8) drew to within five points with 7:38 left but could get no closer. Dartmouth scored seven of the next nine points. Colin Harris led the Black Knights with 12 points and Matt Bell had 10. The Big Green blocked 10 shots and held Army to 29 percent shooting.
